column6: name: Seventh Presbyterian Church, 1819-1827 description: Sheriff Street. Approximate location. Moved from Grand, corner of Goerick. Moved to Broome and Ridge Streets in 1827. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1819
name: Provost Street Baptist Church, 1825-1829 description: Approximate location. Denomination: Baptist Date Founded/Built: 1825

name: Methodist Society Church, 1820?-1830 description: Delancy Street. Approximate location. Moves around the corner and becomes First Methodist Protestant Church in 1830. Denomination: Methodist Date Founded/Built: 1820
name: Prince Street Universalist Church, 1824-1830. description: Corner of Prince and Marion Streets. Sold to Presbyterians in 1830. Denomination: Universalist Date Founded/Built: 1824
name: Elizabeth Street Baptist Church, 1824-1830 description: Approximate location. Meet in "Bethel Free School-House". Denomination: Baptist Date Founded/Built: 1824

name: Third Methodist Society, 1824-1830 description: At Sullivan Street location "preaching was commenced on that ground in the open air, collections being made at each meeting toward the erection of the proposed building��_�۝ In 1830, become Methodist Protestants. Denomination: Methodist Date Founded/Built: 1824
name: "Swamp Church," (Lutheran), 1766-1831 description: Moved to Walker Street in 1830. Denomination: Lutheran Date Founded/Built: 1766

name: First Colored Presbyterian Church, 1825-1831 description: Meets in Colored Public Primary School after they lose their building on Canal Street. Move to Swamp Church in 1831. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1825

name: Eglise Francaise du St Esprit (Huguenots), 1704-1832 description: Moved from Petticoat Lane in 1704. Moved up to Church Street in 1832. United with Protestant Episcopals in 1803. Denomination: Protestant Episcopalian Date Founded/Built: 1704
name: Shearith Israel, 1730-1833 description: Rebuilt 1817/18. Moved to Crosby Street in 1833/34. Denomination: Jewish Date Founded/Built: 1730
name: Cedar Street Presbyterian Church, 1808-1835 description: Moved up to Duane Street in 1835. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1808
name: Cedar Street Presbyterian Church, 1756-1836 description: Rebuilt 1768. Moved up to Cosby and Grant Streets in 1836. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1756

name: Bowery Village Methodist Episcopal Church, 1795-1836 description: Began as a prayer meeting over John Coutant's grocery. Moved to multi-purpose structure (school-room on ground; meeting-room above) in 1795. First church structure built off of the frame of John Street Meetinghouse in 1818. Denomination: Methodist Date Founded/Built: 1795
name: Bowery Presbyterian Church, 1822-1837 description: Sponsored by Female Missionary Society. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1822
name: Christ Church, Roman Catholic, 1825-1837 description: Purchases former Christ Church Protestant Episcopal. Denomination: Catholic Date Founded/Built: 0017
name: Mulberry Street Baptist Church, 1809-1839 description: Rebuilt in 1817. Denomination: Baptist Date Founded/Built: 1809
name: First Baptist Church, 1760-1841 description: Rebuilt 1802. Denomination: Baptist Date Founded/Built: 1760

name: Mission House Baptist Church, 1827-1841 description: Broome Street beween Cannon and Lewis Streets. Approximate location. Baptists move into the Mission House built by the Young Men's Missionary Society when the Methodists move into their new Willett Street meetinghouse in 1827. The congregation builds the Cannon Street Baptist Church around the corner in 1841. Denomination: Baptist Date Founded/Built: 1827

name: Asbury African Methodist Episcopal Church, 1813-1842 description: Separate from Zion in 1813 and move into congregational church on 54 Elizabeth Street. In 1820, Reunite with Zion for two years, ���sometimes standing with the white churches, in the Methodist Episcopal connection, sometimes with the African Conference of the same name, and sometimes with the Zion church.�۝ In 1826, city directories change from listing it as 54 to 55 Elizabeth Street. Denomination: Methodist Date Founded/Built: 1813
name: Eighth Presbyterian Church, 1821-1842 description: Christopher Street. Moved from room in the Eagle Factory. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1821
name: Laight Street Presbyterian Church, 1825-1843 description: Moved up from Spring Street in 1825. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1825
name: Middle Collegiate Dutch Reformed Church, 1729-1844 description: Sold to the city to become the Post Office in 1844. Denomination: Reformed Dutch Date Founded/Built: 1729

name: First Congregational/Unitarian Church, 1820-1845 description: Chambers Street. Approximate location. Meet prior in a private house before building church. Moves to 548 Broadway in 1845. Denomination: Unitarian Date Founded/Built: 1820

name: First Presbyterian Church, 1719-1846 description: Frame meetinghouse, 1719-1748; rebuilt stone, 1748; rebuilt after Revolution; rebuilt, 1811; rebuilt, 1834. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1719

name: Grace Protestant Episcopal Church, 1808-1846 description: Moved up to a "new and very elegant house" on Broadway on corner of Tenth, in March 1846. Denomination: Protestant Episcopalian Date Founded/Built: 1808

name: St. George's Anglican/Protestant Episcopal Church, 1752-1848 description: Rebuilt 1815. Moved up to Sixteenth Street and Third Avenue in 1848. Denomination: Protestant Episcopalian Date Founded/Built: 1752
name: Laurens Street Baptist Church, 1828-1850 description: Approximate location. Denomination: Baptist Date Founded/Built: 1828

name: Zion Protestant Episcopal Church, 1811-1852 description: Former Lutheran congregation. Worship in a small church on Mott, corner of Cross Street in 1811. It burned in 1815 when feed store across the street catches fire. They temporarily worship in the Eglise Du St Esprit until church reopens in 1818. Moved up to 38th and Madison in 1852. Denomination: Protestant Episcopalian Date Founded/Built: 1811

name: Greene Street Reformed Dutch Church, 1825-1852 description: Greene and Houston Streets. Half of schismatic congregation moved over from the Watch House on corner of Prince and Wooster Streets in 1825. Denomination: Reformed Dutch Date Founded/Built: 1825
name: Northwest Reformed Dutch Church, 1808-1854 description: Franklin Street. Moed to 145 W. 23rd Street in 1854. Denomination: Reformed Dutch Date Founded/Built: 1808

name: Christ Church, Protestant Episcopal, 1823-1854 description: Anthony Street. Moved up from Ann Street in 1823. Rebuilt after fire in 1847. On Weeden. Denomination: Protestant Episcopalian Date Founded/Built: 1823
name: Bleecker Street Presbyterian Church, 1826-1855 description: Moved from room next door. Moved to Fourth Avenue and 22nd Street in 1855. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1826
name: Abyssinian Church, 1809-1856 description: African American congregation. Meets in former Scotch Baptist Church. Denomination: Baptist Date Founded/Built: 1809

name: St Phillip's Protestant Episcopal Church, 1819-1856 description: Church for African American congregation. Burned and rebuilt in 1821. Moves up to W. 35th Street in 1856. Denomination: Protestant Episcopalian Date Founded/Built: 1819

name: Methodist Society, 1820-1856. description: Chrystie Street. Schism from Methodist Episcopal Church. Met in schoolroom at 63 Christie until moving to new structure. Denomination: Methodist Date Founded/Built: 1820

name: Rutgers Presbyterian Church, 1796-1862 description: Rebuild church in 1841. Consolidated with and moved up to Madison Avenue Church, 29th and Madison in 1863. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1796
name: Duane Street Methodist Episcopal Church, 1797-1863 description: Moved in 1863 to a private dwelling. Denomination: Methodist Date Founded/Built: 1818
name: Oliver Street Baptist Church, 1795-1863 description: Rebuilt 1800, 1819, 1843. Denomination: Baptist Date Founded/Built: 1795

name: Greenwich Reformed Dutch Church, 1826-1864 description: Herring Street (now Bleecker and Amos Streets). Moved from wooden church between Amos and Charles Streets in 1826. Denomination: Reformed Dutch Date Founded/Built: 1826
name: St. Stephen Protestant Episcopal Church, 1805-1866 description: Moves to Du St Esprit on W 22nd Street in 1866. Denomination: Protestant Episcopalian Date Founded/Built: 1805

name: Northeast Reformed Dutch Church, 1819-1866 description: Corner of Henry and Market Streets. Became the Presbyterian Church of the Sea and the Land in 1866. Denomination: Reformed Dutch Date Founded/Built: 1819

name: Central Presbyterian Church, 1822-1866 description: Broome Street. Moved from Central School in Mulberry Street. Rebuilt 1854. Absorbed and moved to Fiftieth Street Prebysterian Church, 1866. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1822

name: Harsenville/Bloomingdale Reformed Dutch Church, 1816-1868 description: 68th and Broadway. Approximate location. Congregation began in 1805 when Jacob Harsen and his neighbors founded the church. Build stone structure between 1814 and 1816. Street widened in 1868, so the church is razed, but rebuilt 15 years later. Denomination: Reformed Dutch Date Founded/Built: 1816
name: Unitas Fratrum/Moravian Church, 1751-1869 description: Move up to 154 Lexington Avenue in 1869. Denomination: Moravian Date Founded/Built: 1751
name: North Reformed Dutch Church, 1767-1875 description: Remodeled in 1842. Denomination: Reformed Dutch Date Founded/Built: 1767
name: St. Patrick's Roman Catholic Church, 1815-1879 description: Moved up to Fifth Avenue and East 50th Street in 1879. Denomination: Catholic Date Founded/Built: 1815

name: St Luke's Protestant Episcopal Church, 1822-1886 description: Hudson Street. Built church after meeting in temporary spaces. Burns 1886 and move (eventually) up to 141st Street. Denomination: Protestant Episcopalian Date Founded/Built: 1822
name: Allen Street Methodist Episcopal Church, 1810-1889 description: Moved (?) and rebuilt 1836. Denomination: Methodist Date Founded/Built: 1810

name: Canal Street Presbyterian Church, 1822-1893 description: Moved up from Orange Street in 1822. Also known as the Orange Street and Irish Presbyterian Church. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1824

name: Forsyth Methodist Episcopal Church, 1789-1904 description: Rebuilt 1833. Image painted by William Chappel. Inscription on back: "No. 15/ Infant Funeral 8 young Ladies Born by 8 young ladies/ in White followed by the Widdows & children & [Entering]/ Scene in 2d & Bayard/ now Forsyth St/ the meetinghouse ��� Engine house & Corner Store [3]/ also the Chain across the Street to prohibit the vehicles from Passing in time of Service/ Rev Doct Phoebus pastor/ 1809." Denomination: Methodist Date Founded/Built: 1789

name: St. John's Protestant Episcopal Church, 1807-1909 description: Varick Street. Built from 1803 to 1807 facing St. John's (later Hudson) Park. Park becomes the New York Central and Hudson River Rail Road Freight Depot in 1868. Church closes in 1909. Denomination: Protestant Episcopalian Date Founded/Built: 1807
name: Bedford Street Methodist Episcopal Church, 1810-1913 description: Enlarged 1830; rebuilt 1840. Denomination: Methodist Date Founded/Built: 1810

name: Spring Street Presbyterian Church, 1811-1960s description: Moved from grocery store down the street in 1811. Schism in 1825 led to creation of Laight Street Presbyterian, but this remant stayed behind. Rebuilt church in 1836. Denomination: Presbyterian Date Founded/Built: 1811

name: Trinity Anglican/Protestant Episcopal Church, 1697-present description: Rebuilt 1788 following destruction during the Revolution; rebuilt 1841-46. Denomination: Protestant Episcopalian Date Founded/Built: 1697
name: St. Paul's Protestant Episcopal Church, 1767-present description: Denomination: Protestant Episcopalian Date Founded/Built: -0001
name: John Street Methodist Episcopal Church, 1768- description: Rebuilt 1817, 1841 on same site. Denomination: Methodist Date Founded/Built: 1768
name: St. Mark's Protestant Episcopal Church, 1799- description: Denomination: Protestant Episcopalian Date Founded/Built: 1799

column3: Pearl Street Associate Reformed Presbyterian Church, 1797-1853
Murray Street Associate Reformed Presbyterian Church, 1812-1842
